---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Warehouse Management System | Franco Lopez" description="A custom warehouse management system built from scratch for logistics operations, scanner workflows, inventory, reporting, and customs documents.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <span class="eyebrow">software foundation · logistics systems</span>
    <h1>Warehouse Management System</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A custom WMS built from scratch early in my career for cross-border logistics operations.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="content">
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>
      Logistics operations needed accurate inventory, barcode workflows, customer reporting, and customs
      documentation across multiple facilities and international clients.
    </p>

    <h2>What I built</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Barcode generation and label workflows</li>
      <li>Handheld scanner integration</li>
      <li>Desktop and mobile clients</li>
      <li>Real-time inventory tracking</li>
      <li>Operational reporting</li>
      <li>Customs documentation workflows</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Impact</h2>
    <p>
      The system served 20+ international clients across four facilities. It is an important part of my
      story because it shows that my infrastructure work is grounded in software and business workflows,
      not only tickets, vendors, and administration.
    </p>

    <h2>Why it still matters</h2>
    <p>
      Platform and DevOps work is easier to do well when you understand what applications are trying to
      accomplish. This project gave me that foundation: data models, user workflows, uptime pressure,
      reporting needs, and the operational messiness that software has to absorb.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
